> Find a socket in your set that "just" fits inside the splines on the
> clutch disk.  Test fit it up against the flywheel for "close" fit
> as well where the pilot bearing is.

I've said this before, but most people have a perfect VW clutch alignment
tool already.  It's a Mini-Mag-light AA flashlight.  You use the thin end
to align the disk, them use the fat end to illuminate the hole to check
your work.

George

